  "What does 'differentiating with respect to time' mean in related rates?": "",
  "Taking the derivative with respect to x": "",
  "Taking d/dt of both sides of the equation, treating all variables as functions of t": "",
  "Finding the time at which a function is zero": "",
  "Evaluating the function at a specific time": "",
  "In related rates, we differentiate both sides with respect to t, using the chain rule on each variable since x, y, etc., all depend on t. This produces dx/dt, dy/dt, etc.": "",
